📘 LINUX - SCP & NETWORKING NOTES
==============================


🔹 1. What is SCP?
------------------------------
- SCP (Secure Copy) is a command-line tool to transfer files securely
- Works over SSH (encrypted)

Transfers:
- Local → Remote
- Remote → Local
- Remote → Remote

Benefits:
- Secure (encrypted)
- Uses SSH key pair

🔹 SCP Flow

Local Machine
     ↓
 (SSH Encrypted)
     ↓
Remote Server (EC2)


🔹 2. SCP Syntax
------------------------------
scp [options] source destination


🔹 3. Upload File (Local → EC2)
------------------------------
scp -i <key-name> <file-name> ubuntu@<public-ip>:/home/ubuntu/


🔹 4. Download File (EC2 → Local)
------------------------------
scp -i <key-name> ubuntu@<ec2-ip>:/home/ubuntu/<file-name> .


🔹 5. GUI Tools
------------------------------
WinSCP:
- Windows only
- Drag & drop
- Built-in editor

FileZilla:
- Cross-platform
- Free & open source
- Resume large transfers


🔹 6. What is Computer Networking?
------------------------------
- Connecting multiple devices to:
  • Share data
  • Communicate
  • Access resources (internet, servers)


🔹 7. Types of Networks
------------------------------

LAN (Local Area Network)
- Small area (home, office)
- Fast and reliable

MAN (Metropolitan Area Network)
- Covers a city
- Connects multiple LANs

WAN (Wide Area Network)
- Large area (country/global)
- Example: Internet
| Type | Full Form                 | Area   | Example   |
| ---- | ------------------------- | ------ | --------- |
| LAN  | Local Area Network        | Small  | Home WiFi |
| MAN  | Metropolitan Area Network | City   | ISP       |
| WAN  | Wide Area Network         | Global | Internet  |


🔹 8. Core Networking Components
------------------------------

Hardware:
- Router → connects networks (internet)
- Switch → connects devices in LAN
- Modem → connects to ISP
- Firewall → security layer

Software/Protocols:
- HTTP, TCP, DNS
| Component | Function         | Uses        |
| --------- | ---------------- | ----------- |
| Router    | Connect networks | IP          |
| Switch    | Connect devices  | MAC         |
| Modem     | Connect ISP      | Internet    |
| Firewall  | Security         | Block/Allow |


🔹 9. How Networking Works
------------------------------
Client-Server Model:
1. Client sends request
2. Server processes request
3. Server sends response
4. Client displays result


🔹 10. Cloud Networking
------------------------------
- Networking in cloud (AWS, Azure, GCP)
- No physical hardware

Features:
- Virtual
- Scalable
- Configurable


🔹 11. Traditional vs Cloud
------------------------------
Traditional:
- Physical setup
