🔹 12. Microservices Networking
------------------------------
- App split into multiple services
- Services communicate via network

Components:
- API Gateway
- Services (user, order, payment)
- Database
- Load balancer


🔹 13. Key Networking Terms
------------------------------

LAN:
- Small network (home/office)

Switch:
- Connects devices in LAN
- Uses MAC address

Router:
- Connects networks
- Uses IP address

Subnet:
- Smaller network inside larger network

Firewall:
- Controls traffic (allow/block)

Gateway:
- Entry/exit point of network


🔹 14. Network Flow (How it Works)
------------------------------
1. Laptop sends request
2. Switch forwards inside LAN
3. Router sends to internet
4. Firewall checks traffic
5. Server responds
6. Data returns to client


🔹 15. OSI Model (7 Layers)
------------------------------
OSI = Open System Interconnection

Top → Bottom:

7. Application
- User interaction (browser, apps)

6. Presentation
- Formatting, encryption
- Example: HTTPS

5. Session
- Start/stop connection
- Example: login session

4. Transport
- Data delivery
- TCP (reliable), UDP (fast)

3. Network
- Routing using IP
- Example: India → USA

2. Data Link
- Local delivery
- Uses MAC address

1. Physical
- Hardware layer
- Cables, WiFi
| Layer | Name         | Function       | Example    |
| ----- | ------------ | -------------- | ---------- |
| 7     | Application  | User apps      | Browser    |
| 6     | Presentation | Encryption     | HTTPS      |
| 5     | Session      | Connection     | Login      |
| 4     | Transport    | Delivery       | TCP/UDP    |
| 3     | Network      | Routing        | IP         |
| 2     | Data Link    | Local transfer | MAC        |
| 1     | Physical     | Hardware       | Cable/WiFi |


🔹 16. OSI Memory Trick
------------------------------
All People Seem To Need Data Processing

A → Application
P → Presentation
S → Session
T → Transport
N → Network
D → Data Link
P → Physical


